Articles.Content:
I was switching from a Duna mini-lander that had landed to an equatorial Duna satellite when the game crashed. I presume my memory had ran out, so I went back to turn the game on again and went off to use the bathroom. I came back to this...

(the mini-lander)

I was confused and kinda creeped out, so I clicked the exit button on KSP. KSP didn't close, but that weird block thing disappeared as well as the shadow and lights. I decided to just go into my save, and watched it load. When it did load, I got a "Craft Loading Error" on every single ship I had, not including flags or kerbals on EVA. The parts were all generic like solar panels, etc, and they varied. It was really, really weird. I clicked through R&D, expecting most parts to be missing, but from what I saw most were there. My debris was still loaded into the game from earlier.

I went then to the tracking station where I confirmed everything but flags and kerbals on EVA (one Kerbal on Eve) were missing. I selected a flag on the north pole of Kerbin placed earlier, which loaded OK, then hit F9 to try and load my quicksave from when the Duna mini-lander was ~30 seconds from landing on Duna. Instead, all I could see were Craft Loading Errors, every one of them back again. I clicked through them all and I realized an asteroid was what had been selected.

It's a Class B with an encounter with Kerbin in about a year, but it isn't supposed to hit. What's really unusual is that there seems to be the ARM SRB clipped into it. It's not just wiggling, it's literally stuck in there. I try to move it around and timewarp and the SRB stays perfectly fine inside the asteroid. I rarely use that SRB in particular and the only asteroid I've ever been to was for some reason already in a Kerbin orbit.

My money and science are missing. This morning I downloaded a Shuttle replica from the forums, and it seemed fine. I tried to move the camera into the terrain a bit when I landed the mini-lander to see if I could see the antennas I had pretended were soil samplers and had stuck into the terrain. (I don't know how that would cause a crash, but thats all I can think of.) I have 64-bit PC but I ran the 32-bit version.

Is this common and an easy fix or should I start a new save?

Nope, never seen this before. Are you sure your game is unmodded? Also, it might be worth restarting your computer to see if the problem disappears on its own.

If you go to the "Saves" folder you can create a backup of the entire game folder and keep it tucked away by giving the "paste" a new name and gaming the pasted name.

KSP recognizes games by the folder names in the save folder, so any new folder you create that has the right composite folders and files will be recognized as a valid game, even if it is a copy.

This is my bug fix for career mode problems. I am using it now about every 3 days to back up some inexplicable bug.

Copy and save the last game folder under a new name each time before you load KSP. That way if KSP or some add-on is messed up, your the original of the game is still nice and safe.

You can even keep a copy a nice safe distance from KSP, in case the program needs to be reinstalled and you have a serious corruption problem.
